ues that paul coined the term arsenokoitai deriving it from the lxx of lev two zero one two cf one eight two two and using it for homosexual orientation and behavior the latter of which should be an occasion for church discipline i cor five six and legislation in society one tim one eight one one introduction coincident with the rise of the gay rights movement in recent years has been an increasing focus on the biblical statements regarding homosexuality or sodomy as part of this focus the meaning of the term arsenokoitai used twice by the apostle paul one cor six nine i tim one one zero has received vigorous scrutiny this issue is particularly crucial to contemporary society since so much of modern ethics is shaped by biblical statements more particularly the concern over gay rights and the place of gays or homosexuals in the church and in society require the resolution of biblical interpretation this study of historical linguistic and literary matters will survey and evalutate recent proposals for the meaning of arsenokoitai and present evidence to point to a resolution several writers and their positions represent the modern debate on this word three authors bailey boswell and scroggs have provoked considerable discussion and significantly encouraged the wider acceptance of the homosexual lifestyle in society in the church and in the ministry footnotes one for convenience sake the term homosexual is used to encompass both same sex orientation and same sex behavior the meaning of this term is one of the main considerations of this study two these times are differnt from just over a century ago then p fairbairn pastoral epistles edinburg one eight seven four eight nine one could write of arsenokoitai thit it is a term for which fortunately our language has no proper equivalent unknowingly he thereby touched upon the basis for the contemporary debate and study the present writer endorses the pauline authorship of the pastoral epistles on the basis of internal and external evidence see donald guthrie new testament introduction four th ed one nine nine zero six two one six four nine for an extensive discussion and citation of supporters of the pauline authorship three for example see scroggs influence on m olson untangling the web the other side april one nine eight four two four two nine for a study suggesting a further prohibition of homosexuality in the ot see a phillips unconvering the father s skirt vt three zero one jan one nine eight zero three eight four three for a bibliography of other sources dealing with arsenokoitai see the wisondisc religion indexes ny h wison co one nine eight seven